task.summary: Add neural_network_2 for implementing more efficient version
Add calculations for gradients summing all cases in a mini batch at once
Debug new backprop version, add assertions (not working yet)
Add unit test for comparing old and new version
Calculate difference for biases and weights between old and new version
Made one realisation that may help
Debug, now update_mini_batch seems to yield the same result for both versions

Found the problem: integer division when there should have been a float division, which caused the learning rate to be 9 instead of 3. This was enough to drop the network performance from 95 % correct to 10 % correct.
